140 East 53rd Street, adjoining the S.E. corner of Lexington Ave.
March 28, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

Lexington Avenue, east side, north from 53rd Street, showing in centre St. Peter's German Lutheran Church.

April 9, 1928.

P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

(1)
Lexington Ave., west side, north from 53rd Street, showing at the S.W. corner of 55th Street, the Synagogue of the Congregation Ahawath Chesed Shaar Hashomayim, also known as the Central Synagogue.
January 7, 1928.
P. L. Sperr

(2)
The same, one block northward. Across the top appears the upper portion of the Ritz Tower, at the N.E. corner of Park Ave. and 57th Street.
October 12, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
